 {"id":"bd-mblr.2.2.1","title":"File-backed connection lifecycle matrix tests","description":"Implement lifecycle matrix over real database files: create/open/close/reopen/begin/savepoint/commit/rollback/checkpoint permutations. Output: deterministic lifecycle suite with state-validation checks.","design":"Represent permutations as table-driven cases with shared invariant checks to keep suite maintainable as matrix grows.","acceptance_criteria":"- Lifecycle matrix includes documented permutations and expected final states for each permutation.
- All scenarios run on real files (not in-memory-only shortcuts).
- Failures emit reproducible command/context payloads for fast local replay.","notes":"Prioritize paths with highest production relevance: reopen after commit, nested savepoints, crash-adjacent checkpoints.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-02-12T23:37:52.798593105Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-13T00:04:43.623730611Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.2.2.1","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.2.1.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-12T23:38:32.349165932Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.2.2.1","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.2.2","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-12T23:37:52.798593105Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"bd-mblr.2.2.2","title":"Multi-connection lifecycle and coordination tests","description":"Add multi-connection/process-oriented lifecycle tests to validate coordination, visibility, and lock/epoch interactions on file-backed DBs. Output: reproducible multi-actor scenarios with explicit expectations.","design":"Use a scheduler/step runner abstraction to script actor interleavings without nondeterministic thread timing dependence.","acceptance_criteria":"- Multi-actor tests validate correctness for overlapping transactions, visibility windows, and coordination edge cases.
- Scenarios include deterministic actor scheduling so failures are replayable.
- Assertions explicitly check expected concurrent-writer behavior and conflict boundaries.","notes":"This is where we prove coordination behavior under realistic multi-connection pressure.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-02-12T23:37:53.057550640Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-13T00:04:43.691346233Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.2.2.2","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.2.2","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-12T23:37:53.057550640Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.2.2.2","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.2.2.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-12T23:38:32.602239635Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"bd-mblr.2.3","title":"Fault Injection End-to-End Reliability Tests","description":"Run deterministic fault injection (I/O errors, torn writes, fsync failures, lock races, corruption patterns) through real execution paths and verify recovery/error code invariants. Ensure tests validate root-cause diagnostics, not just pass/fail.","design":"Separate fault injection definition from assertion logic so new profiles can be added without duplicating oracle code.","acceptance_criteria":"- Deterministic fault profiles are executed through real backend paths with invariant-based assertions.
- Recovery expectations include both correctness and diagnostic quality (error codes + context).
- Replay path can reproduce at least one representative failure per fault family.","notes":"Couple outputs to structured logging schema to ensure failure triage is machine-parseable.","status":"deferred","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-02-12T23:23:59.950333359Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-13T01:34:34.178265423Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.2.3","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.1.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-12T23:25:09.474795919Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.2.3","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.2","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-12T23:23:59.950333359Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}],"comments":[{"id":1362,"issue_id":"bd-mblr.2.3","author":"Dicklesworthstone","text":"Queue-hygiene adjustment (2026-02-13): this bead is a coordination container for child implementation beads, so status is set to deferred to keep br ready/bv picks focused on executable leaf work. Scope and acceptance criteria are unchanged; completion is rolled up from children.","created_at":"2026-02-13T01:34:34Z"}]}
